  "text": "I was looking at a diagram of the advancement of magical practice starting from Mount Ruth and ending at Ketter. I was wondering if these corresponded to the colors or the densities. In with malpooth is one, S odd is two, odd and net stop being three, to breath four, so on. Is this correct? I am Ra. This is basically incorrect, although you are upon the correct track of thinking. Each of these stations has a complex number and shading of energy centers as well as some part in various balances the lower, the middle, the high, and the total balance. Thus there are complex colors or rays and complex charges, if you will, in each station.",
